    "created_at": "2019-02-09T10:27:26Z",
    "updated_at": "2019-02-09T10:27:26Z",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "I know that github's implementation of CODEOWNERS has some (relatively serious) flaws, but I still think there are some directories that are worth protecting (e.g. some of the test infrastructure directories tend to get modified in broken ways unless there's some oversight).\r\n\r\nPerhaps the best next move on our side to be actually put together the complaints around complaints of CODEOWNERS implementation, make sure they are files as issues for github.com and try to convince github to fix them.\r\n- the biggest issue from my perspective is  that if I'm already an owner for a subdirectory, I should only need an approval from any other contributor (as opposed to needing another OWNER's approval).\r\n"
  },
